‚Ä¢ 988 Lifeline ‚Äî Call or text 988, or chat at 988lifeline.org (24/7, free, confidential)
‚Ä¢ Crisis Text Line ‚Äî Text HOME to 741741 for support anytime
‚Ä¢ The Trevor Project (LGBTQ+ youth) ‚Äî Text START to 678678 or visit thetrevorproject.org

‚Ä¢ Find international mental-health hotlines at findahelpline.com

Crisis Lifeline (24/7):
If you are in crisis, or you know someone who is, contact the 988 Crisis Lifeline or dial 911
in case of emergency.
‚Ä¢ Call or text 988
‚Ä¢ Learn more & Chat: 988lifeline.org
SAMHSA National Helpline (24/7):
1-800-662-4357 is a confidential, free, 24-hour-a-day, 365-day-a-year, information service,
in English and Spanish. This hotline is dedicated for individuals and family members facing
mental and/or substance use disorders.
Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA) helpline and
online locator for mental health services: https://findtreatment.gov/
Crisis Text Line:
Text MHA to 741741 and you‚Äôll be connected to a trained Crisis Counselor. Crisis Text Line
provides free, text-based support 24/7.
Disaster Distress Helpline (24/7):
Call or text 1-800-985-5990
The Disaster Distress Helpline provides immediate crisis counseling for people
experiencing emotional distress related to any natural or human-caused disaster.

title: PLANTED! "Judas & The Black Messiah" | Racial Disparities in Marijuana Arrests
description:
National Expungement Works: https://newxnow.org/
Defacto Books: https://instagram.com/defactobooks?igshid=MzRlODBiNWFlZA==

Show Notes
Information

- Source: ACLU analysis (https://graphics.aclu.org/marijuana-arrest-report/) 2020
    - https://norml.org/marijuana/fact-sheets/racial-disparity-in-marijuana-arrests/ (2022)
    - What is the ACLU?
        - non-profit legal advocacy organization in the US
        - Pro: has been instrumental in several cases involving First Amendment rights
        - Con: those on the right argue that the ACLU is too progressive and biased in its advocacy
- Facts
    - 43% of drug arrests are marijuana arrests (9 out of 10 of these arrests are for possession)
    - Black people are 3.6 times more likely than white people to be arrested for marijuana possession, despite similar
        - usage rates (in Montana it is 9.6x and Kentucky it is 9.4)
        - this is roughly the same rate as pre-reformation times
        - since 2010, racial disparities in marijuana arrests have actually worsened (Maine and Vermont it inreased after legalization)
    - consequences of marijuana arrests are life-altering
        - parents may lose children in court proceedings
        - disabled may lose health care
        - immigrants face deportation
        - families evicted from public housing
        - finding a job becomes difficult
    - due to systemic racism in the justice system
        - War on Drugs policies disproportionately target people of colour
            - racial profiling is to blame
    - larger issue (https://www.pewtrusts.org/en/research-and-analysis/issue-briefs/2023/05/racial-disparities-persist-in-many-us-jails)
        - "Overrepresentation of Black people in jails is a reflection of disproportionally higher admission rates and longer average lengths of stay for Black individuals than for their White or Hispanic counterparts. And these disparities persist across charge severity, age group, and sex, as well as other metrics"

# **Where to Donate, Sign Petitions, Contact Reps:**

**[The Bail Project](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.google.com/url?q%3Dhttps://bailproject.org/%26amp;sa%3DD%26amp;ust%3D1591420779077000&sa=D&ust=1591420779198000&usg=AFQjCNGUhmk9UJypzu7JUKjeCq9yhdCYdA)**

We believe that paying bail for someone in need is an act of resistance against a system that criminalizes race and poverty and an act of solidarity with local communities and movements for decarceration. Over the next five years, The Bail Project will open dozens of sites in high-need jurisdictions with the goal of paying bail for tens of thousands of low-income Americans, all while collecting stories and data that prove money bail is not necessary to ensure people return to court.

**[Baltimore Action Legal Team](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.google.com/url?q%3Dhttps://www.baltimoreactionlegal.org/community-bail-fund%26amp;sa%3DD%26amp;ust%3D1591420779077000&sa=D&ust=1591420779198000&usg=AFQjCNHuz0bH1r7wFJClj1IE4B5Ni-TXMg)**

BALT is committed to building the power of the local Movement for Black Lives. We take our direction from community-organizing groups who are on the ground, and we respect the leadership of local activists. BALT is committed to anti-racist practices and to black leadership. BALT is dedicated to politically-conscious lawyering and to using creative, collective solutions to support the Movement for Black Lives in Baltimore.

**[Black Lives Matter Foundation](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.google.com/url?q%3Dhttps://secure.actblue.com/donate/ms_blm_homepage_2019%26amp;sa%3DD%26amp;ust%3D1591420779078000&sa=D&ust=1591420779198000&usg=AFQjCNHm17iLX0nL_O21u360gVnQixy9Yg)**

#BlackLivesMatter was founded in 2013 in response to the acquittal of Trayvon Martin‚Äôs murderer. Black Lives Matter Foundation, Inc is a global organization in the US, UK, and Canada, whose mission is to eradicate white supremacy and build local power to intervene in violence inflicted on Black communities by the state and vigilantes.

**[Black Visions Collective - MN](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.google.com/url?q%3Dhttps://www.blackvisionsmn.org/about%26amp;sa%3DD%26amp;ust%3D1591420779078000&sa=D&ust=1591420779198000&usg=AFQjCNHOQl5FdPWbcVZdI4iI30B9N1RBWw)**

Since 2017, Black Visions Collective, has been putting into practice the lessons learned from organizations before us in order to shape a political home for Black people across Minnesota. We aim to center our work in healing and transformative justice principles, intentionally develop our organizations core ‚ÄúDNA‚Äù to ensure sustainability, and develop Minnesota‚Äôs emerging Black leadership to lead powerful campaigns.

**[Fair Fight](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.google.com/url?q%3Dhttps://secure.actblue.com/donate/fair-fight-1%26amp;sa%3DD%26amp;ust%3D1591420779079000&sa=D&ust=1591420779198000&usg=AFQjCNFDBW9G6JIKeSKfSEF2LZbIHZOV8A)**

Founded by Stacey Abrams, promotes fair elections by bringing voter discrimination to light with education programs and election reform advocacy.

**[George Floyd Memorial Fund](https://www.google.com/url?q=https://www.google.com/url?q%3Dhttps://www.gofundme.com/f/georgefloyd%26amp;sa%3DD%26amp;ust%3D1591420779080000&sa=D&ust=1591420779199000&usg=AFQjCNHdPOyl1aFGn1BTVWUu4SWRjNdfeg)**

This fund is established to cover funeral and burial expenses, mental and grief counseling, lodging and travel for all court proceedings, and to assist our family in the days to come as we continue to seek justice for George.¬†A portion of these funds will also go to the Estate of George Floyd for the benefit and care of his children and their educational fund.
